<head rend="h4">§ III<note n="#9"/>.</head>
<p><figure><graphic url="huyg003oeuv10ill158.gif"></graphic>
<figDesc>Fig. 3.</figDesc></figure></p>
<p>Si ut OQ ad MN sive ut MA ad AO ita RK ad IP erit spat. hyperbol. RIPK octuplum spat. hyperb. QMNO.</p>
<p>Sit ST media prop. inter RK, IP. Erit spat. RSTK sive sector hyperb. RSΩ quadruplus spat. QNMO.</p>
<p>Ducta SΩ secet R<hi rend="i">ϕ</hi> in V et ducatur YVW parall. ΩR. Erit spat. RWYΩ duplum sectoris dicti hyperb. RSΩ<note n="#10"/>, ideoque octuplum spatij QNMO; quod cum fit, est RV sive ΩY=<hi rend="i">n</hi> nostrum. Est autem <hi rend="i">nx/a</hi>=<hi rend="i">z</hi> subtangens quaesita.</p>
</div>
